exports[`assembly instructions (PRD §20.4) > covers materials, cut, twist, populate, branch, label, inspect, test 1`] = `
"ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS — motor-controller-harness rev A
Units: mm. Generated from HIR 0.1.0; every step references design object IDs.

Materials
---------
 1. Gather 1x 43020-0800 (Micro-Fit 3.0 plug housing, dual row, 8 circuits) — used by connector:M1.
 2. Gather 1x 43025-0800 (Micro-Fit 3.0 receptacle housing, dual row, 8 circuits) — used by connector:J1.

Cut wires
---------
 3. Cut W1: 20AWG red, 420 mm [VBAT_24V].
 4. Cut W2: 20AWG black, 420 mm [GND].
 5. Cut W3: 24AWG white, length per board [CAN_H].
 6. Cut W4: 24AWG blue, length per board [CAN_L].

Twist pairs
-----------
 7. Twist W3 + W4 together (CAN_PAIR).

Populate connectors
-------------------
 8. Populate J1 (43025-0800, receptacle):
      cavity 1: W1 (VBAT_24V)
      cavity 2: W2 (GND)
      cavity 3: W3 (CAN_H)
      cavity 4: W4 (CAN_L)
 9. Populate M1 (43020-0800, plug):
      cavity 1: W1 (VBAT_24V)
      cavity 2: W2 (GND)
      cavity 3: W3 (CAN_H)
      cavity 4: W4 (CAN_L)

Branch assembly
---------------
10. Route branch main (J1 → M1); 420 mm nominal; sleeve with braided-pet.

Apply labels
------------
11. Apply L1 "MOTOR CTRL A" on main 50 mm from J1.

Inspection
----------
12. Verify every cavity against the pinout table; check seating/lock engagement.
13. Verify wire colors and labels against the schedule.
14. Verify branch lengths and sleeve coverage against the board drawing.

Test
----
15. Run the continuity-test procedure (tests.csv / test-plan.json); record results per test ID.
"
`;

